---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import site from '../../site.config.json';
const c = site.colours;
---
<BaseLayout title="Printix vs PaperCut -- Cloud Print Management Comparison" description="Compare Printix and PaperCut cloud print management platforms. Architecture, native features, deployment approach, and positioning for Australian organisations.">
  <section class="section-pad">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:860px">
      <p class="eyebrow">COMPARE</p>
      <h1 style="font-size:clamp(28px,4vw,42px);font-weight:800;margin-bottom:16px">Printix vs PaperCut</h1>
      <p class="muted" style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:40px">Printix and PaperCut are both established cloud print management platforms. While both address print management, they differ in architecture and platform scope. PaperCut spans multiple products across cloud-native and self-hosted models, while Printix delivers functionality through a single SaaS platform with all features included natively.</p>

      <h2 style="margin-top:40px;margin-bottom:16px">Printix at a glance</h2>
      <p class="muted" style="line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px">Printix is a cloud-native print management platform from Tungsten Automation -- a single SaaS product where all capabilities are delivered natively. No add-on tiers, no feature gating, no separate products to evaluate. Print processing happens locally on endpoints, so print data stays on the local network.</p>
      <p class="muted" style="line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px">A cloud-based driver store automates driver and queue deployment across Windows, Mac, and Chromebook, often reducing print-related support tickets. Secure print release is built in via the Printix App (mobile/web with QR and NFC) and Printix Go -- embedded on major MFD brands including Brother, Canon, Epson, FUJIFILM, HP, Konica Minolta, Kyocera, Lexmark, Ricoh, and Xerox. Capture and scanning with OCR to Email, OneDrive, and SharePoint are native features. Identity integration supports Entra ID, Google Workspace, Okta, and OneLogin.</p>
      <p class="muted" style="line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px">Pricing is per active user -- billed only for users who log in during the billing cycle, with all features included regardless of tier.</p>

      <h2 style="margin-top:40px;margin-bottom:16px">PaperCut at a glance</h2>
      <p class="muted" style="line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px">PaperCut offers a range of print management products spanning cloud-native and self-hosted deployment models. PaperCut Hive is a cloud-native, serverless SaaS solution with driverless printing and cloud administration. PaperCut MF is a feature-rich, self-hosted platform offering advanced reporting, granular policy controls, and deep MFD integration. PaperCut itself notes that organisations needing advanced features not currently in Hive should consider MF.</p>
      <p class="muted" style="line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px">This range gives organisations flexibility to choose a deployment model that matches their environment. PaperCut products support Windows, Mac, Linux, Chromebook, iOS, and Android devices.</p>

      <h2 style="margin-top:40px;margin-bottom:16px">Where each platform is typically preferred</h2>
      <div class="compare-cards">
        <div class="compare-card card-printix">
          <h3 class="card-heading-printix">Printix may suit organisations that</h3>
          <ul class="compare-list list-printix">
            <li>Want a single cloud-native product with all features included natively -- no separate tiers, products, or add-ons to evaluate</li>
            <li>Prioritise streamlined deployment with fewer moving parts, particularly in cloud-first environments</li>
            <li>Need native secure print release across 10+ MFD brands via Printix Go</li>
            <li>Require built-in capture and scanning with OCR as a core feature, not a separate product</li>
            <li>Prefer per-active-user billing -- only pay for users who actually print</li>
            <li>Want automated driver and queue management through a centralised cloud driver store</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="compare-card card-competitor">
          <h3 class="card-heading-competitor">PaperCut may suit organisations that</h3>
          <ul class="compare-list list-competitor">
            <li>Want flexibility to choose between cloud-native (Hive) or self-hosted (MF) deployment</li>
            <li>Require advanced reporting, granular policy controls, or deep MFD integration in PaperCut MF</li>
            <li>Have existing PaperCut deployments and invested infrastructure</li>
            <li>Need Linux server support or highly customised print workflows</li>
            <li>Prefer tiered product options with different feature sets at different price points</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="why-printix">
        <h2 style="margin-bottom:12px">Why organisations choose Printix</h2>
        <p style="line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px">While both platforms provide comprehensive print management capabilities, organisations often choose Printix when they prioritise a simplified, cloud-native approach delivered through a single platform rather than multiple products or deployment models.</p>
        <p style="line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px">Printix provides key capabilities such as secure print release, driver management, and remote printing as native features within one SaaS application. In contrast, PaperCut offers a broader portfolio of products designed to support a wider range of deployment scenarios, which may involve selecting and managing different components depending on organisational requirements.</p>
        <p style="line-height:1.7">This distinction can influence deployment complexity, ongoing administration, and how features are packaged and licensed across environments.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mid-cta">
    <div class="container text-center">
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:8px;color:#fff">See the difference for yourself</h2>
      <p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.8);margin-bottom:20px">All features included. No credit card required. Deploy to your first printer in minutes.</p>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:12px;justify-content:center;flex-wrap:wrap">
        <a href={site.hero.ctaPrimaryUrl} class="btn-primary" style="background:#fff;color:#0E7490;font-weight:700">Start free trial</a>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn-secondary" style="border-color:rgba(255,255,255,0.4);color:#fff">Request a quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-pad">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:860px">
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:16px">Key considerations</h2>
      <p class="muted" style="line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px">Printix delivers all capabilities through a single cloud-native product, while PaperCut provides a portfolio of products (Hive, Pocket, MF, NG) designed for different requirements and deployment preferences. The right choice often depends on whether an organisation values a unified platform with native features or prefers the flexibility of multiple products that can be combined based on specific needs.</p>
      <p class="muted" style="line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px">Pricing models differ. Printix uses per-active-user subscription pricing with all features included. PaperCut pricing varies by product tier. Organisations should request current pricing from each vendor, as models and rates may change.</p>

      <p class="muted compare-disclaimer" style="font-size:13px;margin-top:32px;font-style:italic">This comparison is based on publicly available information and general product positioning as of March 2026. Features, capabilities, and pricing may vary depending on configuration, version, and deployment model. Verify current details directly with each vendor before making purchasing decisions.</p>
      <p class="muted compare-disclaimer" style="font-size:13px;margin-top:12px;font-style:italic">PaperCut is a registered trademark of PaperCut Software International Pty Ltd. This site is not affiliated with or endorsed by PaperCut. Printix is a product of Tungsten Automation.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-pad section-dark" style="padding:60px 0">
    <div class="container text-center">
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:12px">Try Printix free for 30 days</h2>
      <p class="muted" style="margin-bottom:24px">All features included. No credit card required.</p>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:12px;justify-content:center;flex-wrap:wrap"><a href={site.hero.ctaPrimaryUrl} class="btn-primary">Start free trial</a><a href="/contact" class="btn-secondary" style="border-color:rgba(255,255,255,0.3);color:#fff">Request a quote</a></div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <style is:inline>
    .eyebrow{font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:var(--brand);letter-spacing:0.06em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:12px}
    .compare-cards{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:24px;margin-top:24px}
    .card-printix{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#0891B2 0%,#0E7490 100%);border-radius:12px;padding:28px;color:#fff}
    .card-competitor{background:var(--neutral);border-radius:12px;padding:28px}
    .card-heading-printix{font-size:18px;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:12px;color:#fff}
    .card-heading-competitor{font-size:18px;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:12px;color:var(--muted)}
    .compare-list{list-style:none;padding:0}
    .compare-list li{position:relative;padding-left:20px;font-size:15px;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:8px}
    .list-printix li{color:rgba(255,255,255,0.92)}
    .list-printix li::before{content:'\2713';position:absolute;left:0;color:#22D3EE;font-weight:700}
    .list-competitor li{color:var(--muted)}
    .list-competitor li::before{content:'\2713';position:absolute;left:0;color:var(--muted);font-weight:700}
    .why-printix{margin-top:40px;background:linear-gradient(135deg,#ECFEFF 0%,#F0FDFA 100%);border-radius:16px;padding:32px;border:1px solid #A5F3FC}
    .why-printix h2{color:#0E7490}
    .why-printix p{color:#115E59;margin:0}
    .why-printix p+p{margin-top:12px}
    .mid-cta{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#0891B2 0%,#0E7490 100%);padding:48px 0;margin:0}
    .mid-cta h2{font-size:clamp(22px,3vw,30px)}
    @media(max-width:768px){.compare-cards{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
